1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,920
Rituals, beliefs, and myths in this series are a work of fiction and in no regard refer to religions or faiths of any certain cultures.

2
00:00:12,640 --> 00:00:15,760
Fate is woven by three forces.

3
00:00:16,160 --> 00:00:16,880
Heaven.

4
00:00:17,280 --> 00:00:17,920
Earth.

5
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:18,880
Humanity.

6
00:00:19,520 --> 00:00:23,440
However, the fate of some is made to be
more complicated than that.

7
00:00:31,080 --> 00:00:32,080
You know what that thing is?

8
00:00:32,360 --> 00:00:33,120
It’s called ‘yao.’

9
00:00:33,280 --> 00:00:34,680
It is born against nature.

10
00:00:34,880 --> 00:00:35,840
In defiance of heaven and earth.

11
00:00:36,040 --> 00:00:37,680
In defiance even of death.

12
00:00:37,920 --> 00:00:38,920
How come I can see it?

13
00:00:39,920 --> 00:00:41,040
Because you are one of them.

14
00:00:41,640 --> 00:00:42,880
The tattoo behind your ear.

15
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:45,120
It is a seal.

16
00:00:45,760 --> 00:00:47,160
That’s why you can see them.

17
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:02,240
Hey!

18
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:03,120
Wizard’s grandkid!

19
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:04,720
Oh, he’s gonna put a curse on us.

20
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:06,520
Run before he hexes us!

21
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:29,120
BETONG, YALA, 2012

22
00:02:38,640 --> 00:02:40,200
I appreciate your visit,

23
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:43,240
but I have come too far

24
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:45,760
to go back.

25
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:47,480
But this time,

26
00:02:47,480 --> 00:02:50,480
we did not come here to talk about you.

27
00:02:51,160 --> 00:02:55,200
We are here to talk about your grandson.

28
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:59,640
Yong Le is still young and doesn’t show any potential.

29
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:07,680
Our ancestral expertise needs to be passed down. Please consider.

30
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:14,880
(When I was young, I used to wonder if Gung was a sorcerer.)

31
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:23,880
I am no sorcerer like everyone is saying.

32
00:03:25,720 --> 00:03:27,360
I have no superpower.

33
00:03:28,040 --> 00:03:32,240
I am just a man who can connect with a great force,

34
00:03:32,680 --> 00:03:36,600
and borrow that power for a period of time.

35
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,120
A great force?

36
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:46,560
What kind of force is it, Gung?

37
00:03:48,440 --> 00:03:50,040
The power of heaven and earth.

38
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:54,079
You can say it is the force of nature.

39
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:59,600
That’s why Wu needs to protect the earth and nature.

40
00:04:00,760 --> 00:04:03,680
That is every Wu’s ‘tianming.’

41
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:06,240
Will I ever become Wu like you, Gung?

42
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:16,959
That is for heaven and earth to decide.

43
00:05:56,920 --> 00:05:57,400
Hey.

44
00:05:57,840 --> 00:05:59,400
So this thing about the yao in my body…

45
00:05:59,680 --> 00:06:00,480
What should I do?

46
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:05,520
I don’t know.

47
00:06:06,520 --> 00:06:07,600
What do you think you should do?

48
00:06:08,080 --> 00:06:08,920
You can help me, right?

49
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:13,400
Can you exorcise it or…
do whatever to get it out of my body?

50
00:06:14,880 --> 00:06:15,360
Sure thing.

51
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:19,160
But I’ll have to destroy its vessel.

52
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:21,120
And that is you.

53
00:06:22,080 --> 00:06:22,800
More importantly,

54
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:26,640
I don’t know what kind of yao it is,
and why it’s inhabited in your body.

55
00:06:27,080 --> 00:06:29,400
Without that kind of information, there’s just nothing I can do.

56
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:34,400
Damn it.

57
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:36,040
Come on.

58
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:38,720
Just think of it as a benign tumor.

59
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:42,120
As long as it’s not cancer,
you can go on living your life.

60
00:06:42,960 --> 00:06:43,920
You get to keep on breathing.

61
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:44,800
Wow.

62
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:47,040
You’re a jerk, you know that?

63
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:55,720
Your paycheck.

64
00:06:58,720 --> 00:06:59,200
Whoa.

65
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:02,920
You’re giving me this much for a few days
of chauffeuring you around?

66
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:04,200
You did more than that.

67
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:06,600
You helped me defeat yao.

68
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:09,160
Oh, I see.

69
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:10,400
You’re right.

70
00:07:11,280 --> 00:07:12,320
I actually deserve even more.

71
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:15,480
You and your money problem…

72
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:17,840
But you overestimated yourself.

73
00:07:18,760 --> 00:07:21,840
The truth is, even without you,

74
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:23,960
I would have easily defeated that yao anyway.

75
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:28,400
The only reason I let you tag along
was because I needed to check that

76
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:30,720
besides seeing yao,

77
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:36,920
if you’re useful enough for the next big job.

78
00:07:39,280 --> 00:07:41,760
I need to suppress that yaoat the gambling house.

79
00:07:43,840 --> 00:07:47,480
It was born from a curse performed by the owner
when the place was established.

80
00:07:47,880 --> 00:07:53,720
When it’s mature enough,
it has enough power to alter the fate of gamblers.

81
00:07:54,560 --> 00:07:56,200
No matter how lucky a person is,

82
00:07:57,320 --> 00:08:00,760
yao can alter their fortuneand make them hapless,

83
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:04,800
just so it can keep feeding on their despair.

84
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:07,280
And how would you suppress it?

85
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:10,960
Like, tear the whole place down?

86
00:08:10,960 --> 00:08:12,360
Of course not.

87
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:15,280
I just need to enshrine it in a smaller vessel

88
00:08:15,960 --> 00:08:16,600
and seal it.

89
00:08:17,200 --> 00:08:20,560
This is what I really need your help with.

90
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:24,200
I see.

91
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:26,760
What you mean to say is…

92
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:31,120
My paycheck will at least be more fair than this, right?

93
00:08:31,440 --> 00:08:31,920
A million.

94
00:08:32,799 --> 00:08:33,559
Fair enough for you?

95
00:08:38,760 --> 00:08:39,240
Deal.

96
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:48,680
NIRAN

97
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:56,440
Damn it.

98
00:08:57,760 --> 00:08:58,280
Hello?

99
00:08:58,680 --> 00:08:59,240
(You ready?)

100
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:00,520
What?

101
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:01,840
It’s today?

102
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:07,880
I’m here!

103
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:09,880
I’m here.

104
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:15,040
That was exhausting.

105
00:09:18,480 --> 00:09:19,440
Don’t look at me like that.

106
00:09:20,880 --> 00:09:23,240
You said we’d do it on Saturday.

107
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:27,160
Shit.

108
00:09:27,880 --> 00:09:28,680
Saturday...

109
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:30,840
I guess today’s Saturday.

110
00:09:32,560 --> 00:09:33,720
Well, here I am!

111
00:09:37,080 --> 00:09:37,840
I pay in advance.

112
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:40,920
So you have enough cash for the table.

113
00:09:42,120 --> 00:09:44,040
Holy crap!

114
00:09:45,920 --> 00:09:47,040
Whoa.

115
00:09:47,640 --> 00:09:50,880
If you win the game, that whole thing is your paycheck.

116
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:56,880
Are you sure you’re ready?

117
00:09:58,480 --> 00:09:59,160
Of course, I am.

118
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:00,880
Jerk.

119
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:02,360
There’s still goop in your eye.

120
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:05,720
What the hell?

121
00:10:16,160 --> 00:10:17,000
I think we should call it off.

122
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:17,560
What?

123
00:10:18,160 --> 00:10:18,840
For wasting your time.

124
00:10:20,040 --> 00:10:21,000
Wait, wait, wait.

125
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:23,240
Wait a minute.

126
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:25,800
You don’t trust me at all, do you?

127
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:32,280
Okay.

128
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:33,680
I’m sorry.

129
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:35,280
I was late.

130
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:40,200
I know I’m pretty much sleep-deprived,
but I swear my head’s in the right place.

131
00:10:40,320 --> 00:10:42,120
My brain’s functioning fine and ready to work for you.

132
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:43,400
I’ll do my best.

133
00:10:43,680 --> 00:10:44,440
You won’t be disappointed in m—

134
00:10:44,440 --> 00:10:45,080
Enough.

135
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:47,240
I just don’t want to put your life at risk.

136
00:10:56,920 --> 00:10:58,360
If I make one wrong move,

137
00:10:59,160 --> 00:11:03,200
the person whose soul will be lost to yao
will be you, not me.

138
00:11:07,160 --> 00:11:10,160
That means you’ll die.

139
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:14,840
To hell with it.

140
00:11:15,120 --> 00:11:16,920
My life isn’t worth all that much anyway.

141
00:11:16,920 --> 00:11:17,640
You asshole.

142
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:19,360
Who taught you to think of your life that way?

143
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:29,880
Come on.

144
00:11:30,560 --> 00:11:31,400
I won’t die.

145
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:35,240
I know you’ll defeat that yao.

146
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:40,480
You…

147
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:44,400
You believe in me?

148
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:45,520
Hell yeah!

149
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:48,160
I saw you defeat yao with my own eyes.

150
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:49,880
You’re freaking amazing.

151
00:11:50,840 --> 00:11:51,280
Alright?

152
00:11:51,880 --> 00:11:52,760
Let’s get on with it.

153
00:11:53,840 --> 00:11:56,040
I’ll do my best and win the game.

154
00:11:56,040 --> 00:11:56,560
Alright?

155
00:11:57,400 --> 00:11:58,240
Let’s do it.

156
00:12:02,040 --> 00:12:02,680
Well, then…

157
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:04,960
Can I trust you?

158
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:06,200
Of course, you can!

159
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:08,920
You can so freaking count on me.

160
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:26,920
I’ll do my best.

161
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:30,160
This is how it begins, isn’t it?

162
00:12:30,760 --> 00:12:32,040
I believe in you.

163
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:33,480
You believe in me.

164
00:12:34,520 --> 00:12:35,600
We trust each other.

165
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:37,960
Everything will work out alright.

166
00:12:41,520 --> 00:12:42,680
I’ll win.

167
00:12:46,280 --> 00:12:46,760
Hey.

168
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:47,280
Wait!

169
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:00,960
Give me a million.

170
00:13:01,880 --> 00:13:03,400
Did you rob a damn bank or something?

171
00:13:03,720 --> 00:13:04,200
Hell yeah.

172
00:13:04,560 --> 00:13:06,960
And the next place on my list to rob is here.

173
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:12,960
What’s next?

174
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:13,920
Here’s the plan

175
00:13:14,480 --> 00:13:17,120
Since you can see yao,

176
00:13:18,040 --> 00:13:20,120
you have to play against it…

177
00:13:21,880 --> 00:13:22,680
with your soul.

178
00:13:27,520 --> 00:13:28,200
One million.

179
00:13:29,240 --> 00:13:33,160
Your job is to keep playing until yao comes out to get you.

180
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:37,920
Meanwhile, I’ll get the ritual set up.

181
00:13:38,520 --> 00:13:42,000
There’s a basement they use to hide gamblers in case of a police raid.

182
00:13:42,760 --> 00:13:45,680
It’s the perfect spot for the ritual.

183
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:48,640
Hang on.

184
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:51,640
You said yao turns people hapless.

185
00:13:52,080 --> 00:13:53,720
Then I won’t win no matter how I play the game.

186
00:13:54,640 --> 00:13:55,040
Don’t worry.

187
00:13:56,040 --> 00:13:57,360
I’ll enhance your fortune with a ritual.

188
00:13:58,320 --> 00:14:01,320
This ritual will set your fate in alignment with heaven,

189
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:02,720
independent from yao’s influence.

190
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:16,720
Small blind.

191
00:14:17,040 --> 00:14:17,600
Big blind.

192
00:14:20,880 --> 00:14:22,840
Now that your luck is dictated by heaven,

193
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:25,200
when you think your cards are good enough,

194
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:33,840
you need to bet against yao with your soul.

195
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:35,800
Four thousand.

196
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:40,320
When yao loses, its power weakens.

197
00:14:40,920 --> 00:14:42,320
And I can seal it.

198
00:14:42,440 --> 00:14:43,040
Alright!

199
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:44,800
If it’s fair game, I’ll definitely win.

200
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:46,240
There’s a catch.

201
00:14:46,520 --> 00:14:48,560
The fortune enhancement ritual only lasts so long,

202
00:14:49,360 --> 00:14:51,360
even shorter where yao’s influence is strong.

203
00:14:52,120 --> 00:14:54,360
So you need to hurry up and win the game.

204
00:14:54,760 --> 00:14:57,240
Don’t forget that if you lose…

205
00:14:57,600 --> 00:14:58,160
Flop.

206
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:00,080
Check.

207
00:15:00,080 --> 00:15:00,680
Check.

208
00:15:00,920 --> 00:15:01,400
Check.

209
00:15:02,760 --> 00:15:03,680
A hundred thousand.

210
00:15:05,760 --> 00:15:06,480
A hundred thousand.

211
00:15:07,640 --> 00:15:08,680
…you won’t just lose the money,

212
00:15:09,840 --> 00:15:11,320
but also your soul.

213
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:17,120
A hundred thousand.

214
00:15:21,760 --> 00:15:22,320
Turn.

215
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:26,120
Check.

216
00:15:26,440 --> 00:15:27,000
Check.

217
00:15:27,800 --> 00:15:28,800
Another one hundred thousand.

218
00:15:29,520 --> 00:15:30,200
A hundred thousand.

219
00:15:32,480 --> 00:15:33,040
Well?

220
00:15:34,440 --> 00:15:35,120
Raised.

221
00:15:35,680 --> 00:15:36,320
River.

222
00:15:37,880 --> 00:15:38,600
Please show your hands.

223
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:41,760
Two pairs, aces and kings.

224
00:15:44,080 --> 00:15:45,720
Five-high straight, kiddo.

225
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:49,200
Hey.

226
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:50,320
You sure you got this?

227
00:15:50,720 --> 00:15:52,080
You spooked me, you jerk.

228
00:15:54,560 --> 00:15:55,880
Did you even perform that ritual?

229
00:15:56,880 --> 00:15:57,640
Of course I did.

230
00:15:58,360 --> 00:15:59,280
Goddamn it.

231
00:15:59,640 --> 00:16:02,480
Your luck freaking sucks.

232
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:04,040
You should quit gambling.

233
00:16:04,040 --> 00:16:04,640
Ugh!

234
00:16:05,080 --> 00:16:05,560
Shh.

235
00:16:11,120 --> 00:16:11,640
Ten thousand.

236
00:16:11,680 --> 00:16:12,760
Two hundred thousand.

237
00:16:14,480 --> 00:16:14,960
Fold.

238
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:18,880
I made a big mistake choosing you.

239
00:16:19,080 --> 00:16:21,160
Stop freaking babbling.

240
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:25,080
You might wanna listen to your buddy.

241
00:16:28,520 --> 00:16:29,160
Or your boyfriend?

242
00:16:35,720 --> 00:16:38,200
Ever heard of a poker face, you asshole?

243
00:16:39,280 --> 00:16:39,800
Flop.

244
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:41,840
Check.

245
00:16:42,920 --> 00:16:43,760
A hundred thousand.

246
00:16:44,920 --> 00:16:45,440
River.

247
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:48,320
Pair of kings.

248
00:16:49,640 --> 00:16:50,760
Pair of aces.

249
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:54,600
A hundred thousand.

250
00:16:56,560 --> 00:16:57,040
Fold.

251
00:16:57,240 --> 00:16:58,880
How about you go home and tuck into bed?

252
00:17:09,920 --> 00:17:10,480
Fold.

253
00:17:16,119 --> 00:17:16,960
Hey, let’s just go.

254
00:17:18,160 --> 00:17:18,960
Take it easy.

255
00:17:33,640 --> 00:17:34,800
I think this is it.

256
00:17:40,280 --> 00:17:40,800
All in.

257
00:17:41,080 --> 00:17:41,720
All in.

258
00:17:43,480 --> 00:17:44,240
I’ll bet on this, too.

259
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:45,080
You bastard!

260
00:17:45,280 --> 00:17:45,760
Hey.

261
00:17:46,320 --> 00:17:47,480
Please don’t make a scene.

262
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:48,240
I’m not.

263
00:17:48,840 --> 00:17:52,480
This classic car is worth almost two million, you know?

264
00:17:52,640 --> 00:17:54,600
I’ll give it to you right now for one million.

265
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:56,040
You up for it, man?

266
00:18:01,440 --> 00:18:01,920
Sure.

267
00:18:08,320 --> 00:18:09,000
How about that?

268
00:18:09,920 --> 00:18:11,880
Or is there anything else you’d wanna bet on?

269
00:18:12,240 --> 00:18:15,200
Your mom? Your wife? Your sister?

270
00:18:16,400 --> 00:18:18,960
Keep that lousy mouth for dinner, asshole.

271
00:18:20,640 --> 00:18:21,520
No need.

272
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:28,520
I’ll have you crying when I get all your money, you little shit.

273
00:18:28,840 --> 00:18:29,360
Alright.

274
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:32,320
We’ll see who’s going home with an empty pocket.

275
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:36,040
I bet on this with my life and my damn soul.

276
00:18:48,880 --> 00:18:49,640
Damn it!

277
00:18:50,840 --> 00:18:51,480
Fold.

278
00:18:52,040 --> 00:18:52,520
Fold.

279
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:53,360
Fold.

280
00:20:25,720 --> 00:20:26,520
Hell yeah!

281
00:20:26,760 --> 00:20:27,280
I won!

282
00:20:28,880 --> 00:20:30,280
I won, you bastard!

283
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:31,480
I won!

284
00:22:03,920 --> 00:22:04,400
Fuck!

285
00:22:04,560 --> 00:22:05,600
Let go of me!

286
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:06,520
What the hell are you doing?

287
00:22:08,560 --> 00:22:09,760
You cheated, didn’t you?

288
00:22:09,760 --> 00:22:12,040
Cheated, my ass! What the fuck’s wrong with you?

289
00:22:12,040 --> 00:22:13,160
I have four cards!

290
00:22:13,240 --> 00:22:14,520
How could I have lost?

291
00:22:14,640 --> 00:22:14,960
Huh?

292
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:17,760
Why don’t you light some incense and ask the gods, you jerk?

293
00:22:29,800 --> 00:22:30,880
Bastard!

294
00:23:02,480 --> 00:23:03,840
You… Die!

295
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:20,640
Who… Are… You?

296
00:23:25,320 --> 00:23:26,880
Wizard’s grandkid. Wizard’s grandkid.

297
00:23:28,840 --> 00:23:29,880
Wu Yong Le!

298
00:23:56,440 --> 00:23:57,400
Who…

299
00:23:58,280 --> 00:23:58,960
Are…

300
00:23:59,840 --> 00:24:00,680
You?

301
00:24:52,640 --> 00:24:53,000
Damn it.

302
00:24:53,120 --> 00:24:55,000
God forbid a man just earn his hard work.

303
00:24:55,120 --> 00:24:56,960
Does he have to risk his life and exhaust himself?

304
00:24:57,320 --> 00:24:58,320
Damn it.

305
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:03,640
Yeah, you’re a bit late, guys.

306
00:25:04,320 --> 00:25:06,040
Hey, I need my chips exchanged!

307
00:25:18,280 --> 00:25:19,240
You look like you’ve seen better days.

308
00:25:20,960 --> 00:25:21,840
I could say the same about you.

309
00:25:22,960 --> 00:25:23,520
All done?

310
00:25:26,840 --> 00:25:29,640
How’d you know you’d win with those cards?

311
00:25:35,040 --> 00:25:35,480
I don’t know.

312
00:25:37,840 --> 00:25:39,960
I just… felt it.

313
00:25:41,440 --> 00:25:41,920
I don’t know.

314
00:25:42,680 --> 00:25:43,400
I don’t know why.

315
00:25:45,560 --> 00:25:47,080
Either your mind was playing tricks on you,

316
00:25:48,360 --> 00:25:50,320
or it was heaven, giving you a sign.

317
00:25:52,320 --> 00:25:53,560
I think it’s the latter.

318
00:25:54,920 --> 00:25:57,200
And the one whose mind’s playing tricks on him is you.

319
00:26:06,760 --> 00:26:07,640
I hate gambling.

320
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:19,520
Let’s play with real money.

321
00:26:19,520 --> 00:26:19,960
Yeah!

322
00:26:20,040 --> 00:26:20,920
Let’s do it!

323
00:26:20,920 --> 00:26:23,480
Let’s play with real money!

324
00:26:23,600 --> 00:26:24,520
You scared?

325
00:26:24,640 --> 00:26:28,280
I thought you have the power of nature, you wizard’s grandkid!

326
00:27:15,320 --> 00:27:17,240
I GOT IT. HANDOVER TOMORROW. BRING THE MONEY.

327
00:27:31,040 --> 00:27:32,680
HOUSE FOR SALE WITH LAND

328
00:27:32,800 --> 00:27:33,160
Uncle?

329
00:27:33,400 --> 00:27:35,120
I wired you one million as a deposit.

330
00:27:37,320 --> 00:27:38,800
Forget where I got it from.

331
00:27:39,320 --> 00:27:41,120
It’s my house. I want it back.

332
00:27:47,480 --> 00:27:47,720
PLOY

333
00:27:47,720 --> 00:27:48,400
I BOUGHT THE HOUSE BACK FROM UNCLE.

334
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:49,800
YOU CAN MOVE BACK IN.

335
00:29:06,240 --> 00:29:08,640
BIRTH CERTIFICATE

336
00:29:13,320 --> 00:29:15,640
TOTAL HEARING IMPAIRMENT

337
00:29:49,760 --> 00:29:51,600
MIDDAY NEWS

338
00:29:51,960 --> 00:29:52,760
Good morning.

339
00:29:52,760 --> 00:29:56,440
It is 11.07 a.m. and you’re with Midday News.

340
00:29:56,440 --> 00:29:58,840
It’s been less than a year since the national election,

341
00:29:58,840 --> 00:30:01,520
but there’s an interesting development.

342
00:30:01,520 --> 00:30:03,560
There is a leaked photo.

343
00:30:03,560 --> 00:30:06,720
PM’S LEAKED PHOTO WITH BAO CHENG SPARKS DEBATES
The person in the photo isnone other than the Prime Minister,

344
00:30:07,160 --> 00:30:09,480
next to Mr. Bao Cheng.

345
00:30:09,680 --> 00:30:12,440
Mr. Bao Cheng, as words on the street suggest,

346
00:30:12,680 --> 00:30:15,360
is the big boss mafia of Ratchada.

347
00:30:15,400 --> 00:30:17,760
(The photo was taken a long time ago,)

348
00:30:17,800 --> 00:30:19,120
(before the election.)

349
00:30:19,200 --> 00:30:21,600
(But the people can’t help but question)

350
00:30:21,600 --> 00:30:26,040
(why the leader of our nation would be in cahoots with a man like him.)

351
00:30:26,040 --> 00:30:30,880
(That is the reason why people are gathering up in masses,)

352
00:30:31,200 --> 00:30:35,000
(calling for the Prime Minister to step down from his role.)

353
00:30:35,040 --> 00:30:38,680
(We will keep you up to date on this topic.)

354
00:30:44,760 --> 00:30:45,960
I found this at home.

355
00:30:46,280 --> 00:30:47,600
Do you know what it is?

356
00:30:49,640 --> 00:30:51,280
I also just learned that I was born deaf.

357
00:31:02,360 --> 00:31:02,800
Okay.

358
00:31:04,040 --> 00:31:04,960
I got it wrong.

359
00:31:07,440 --> 00:31:11,160
What you have inside you is much stronger than yao.

360
00:31:12,480 --> 00:31:13,400
It’s a demon.

361
00:31:14,920 --> 00:31:16,520
And this demon…

362
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:19,400
is the Six-Eared Macaque.

363
00:31:25,320 --> 00:31:30,440
Yao that avoid being suppressed and live long enough to absorb the power of nature

364
00:31:31,400 --> 00:31:32,640
become demons.

365
00:31:34,280 --> 00:31:37,280
Its power rivals that of heaven and earth.

366
00:31:38,760 --> 00:31:41,520
This demon, ‘Liu er mihou,’

367
00:31:43,000 --> 00:31:47,400
is the Six-Eared Macaque with heavenly hearing.

368
00:31:52,800 --> 00:31:55,560
Legend goes this demon was suppressed

369
00:31:56,520 --> 00:31:58,560
by having his soul ripped into thousands of shreds.

370
00:31:59,440 --> 00:32:04,520
I’d say what’s inside you is one in a thousand,

371
00:32:05,320 --> 00:32:06,520
or possibly even smaller.

372
00:32:07,960 --> 00:32:09,960
But that’s dangerous enough as it is.

373
00:32:11,440 --> 00:32:13,480
All this just to cure hearing impairment?

374
00:32:14,760 --> 00:32:15,280
Shit.

375
00:32:16,280 --> 00:32:17,760
Who the hell was crazy enough to perform this ritual?

376
00:32:18,680 --> 00:32:19,720
Can’t say I don’t admire their guts, though.

377
00:32:23,360 --> 00:32:24,200
What do I do?

378
00:32:24,720 --> 00:32:25,400
You don’t.

379
00:32:26,240 --> 00:32:27,040
There’s nothing to be done.

380
00:32:30,120 --> 00:32:30,640
What?

381
00:32:32,000 --> 00:32:32,720
What do you mean?

382
00:32:36,480 --> 00:32:37,880
Picture this.

383
00:32:38,920 --> 00:32:40,320
You have a bomb in your stomach.

384
00:32:41,040 --> 00:32:43,240
I’m the idiot who’s stupid enough to cut you up to retrieve it.

385
00:32:43,640 --> 00:32:45,040
If I mess up and it goes off,

386
00:32:45,520 --> 00:32:46,280
we’re doomed!

387
00:32:46,760 --> 00:32:48,200
We’ll both get ourselves killed.

388
00:32:48,800 --> 00:32:49,720
Just leave it like this.

389
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:50,880
It’s safer that way.

390
00:32:52,760 --> 00:32:53,080
What?

391
00:32:55,280 --> 00:32:57,360
But you said the seal has weakened.

392
00:32:57,920 --> 00:32:59,680
You’d better pray it’s temporary.

393
00:33:00,760 --> 00:33:02,360
Because if the seal’s broken…

394
00:33:04,840 --> 00:33:05,640
It’s every man for himself.

395
00:33:07,400 --> 00:33:08,240
I have things to do. Gotta go.

396
00:33:08,400 --> 00:33:09,080
Hey, wait.

397
00:33:10,600 --> 00:33:12,000
“It’s every man for himself,” my ass!

398
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:13,400
What the hell do you mean to say?

399
00:33:16,480 --> 00:33:19,000
I mean you will be devoured by that demon.

400
00:33:19,520 --> 00:33:21,280
When that happens, no one can save you.

401
00:33:25,440 --> 00:33:26,200
What the hell?

402
00:33:54,840 --> 00:33:56,600
That thing is sealed in here?

403
00:33:57,240 --> 00:33:57,640
Yeah.

404
00:33:58,160 --> 00:33:58,560
That’s the stuff.

405
00:33:59,200 --> 00:33:59,760
Careful with that.

406
00:34:00,600 --> 00:34:01,520
Don’t let it suck away all your good luck.

407
00:34:23,840 --> 00:34:26,840
MR. TAWIT ANANTARAKARN
TEN MILLION BAHT

408
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:04,600
I’ve never seen anything so powerful before.

409
00:35:05,680 --> 00:35:06,840
This is the man who sold it to us.

410
00:35:12,840 --> 00:35:16,200
If it isn’t one of the highly esteemed Suming.

411
00:35:27,440 --> 00:35:30,280
(Following the raid on a gambling house in Bangkok,)

412
00:35:30,280 --> 00:35:33,800
(the investigation is still ongoing as to who is behind the illegal casino.)

413
00:35:33,880 --> 00:35:38,520
CASINO RAIDED AND BAO CHENG DENATULARIZED
(The raid on this gambling house is made possible by the government policy)

414
00:35:38,520 --> 00:35:43,400
(to quell the raging illegal businesses owned by foreign mafias in Thailand.)

415
00:35:43,400 --> 00:35:46,520
(The Prime Minister reassures that within the next month,)

416
00:35:46,520 --> 00:35:49,520
(his government will wipe the country clean of these mafias,)

417
00:35:49,720 --> 00:35:53,520
(but more specifically Mr. Tanarat Jongrattana, or Bao Cheng,)

418
00:35:53,600 --> 00:35:57,280
(who is a suspect behind the Huai Khwang nightclubs and money laundering cases.)

419
00:35:57,480 --> 00:36:00,880
(Bao Cheng is a naturalized Thai citizen through marriage,)

420
00:36:00,880 --> 00:36:04,520
(before being arrested for money laundering at the beginning of this year.)

421
00:36:04,520 --> 00:36:07,200
(The investigation is still ongoing.)

422
00:36:07,240 --> 00:36:10,680
(However, a committee has been appointed to work on denaturalization…)

423
00:36:10,680 --> 00:36:11,480
Master.

424
00:36:13,960 --> 00:36:16,600
This is the yao from our rival’s casino.

425
00:36:17,240 --> 00:36:19,360
Once it was sealed,

426
00:36:19,600 --> 00:36:22,280
that casino was immediately raided.

427
00:36:22,880 --> 00:36:27,520
All you need to do is have me place it in your casino,

428
00:36:27,640 --> 00:36:32,360
and you will rule over all of Bangkok.

429
00:36:44,800 --> 00:36:45,600
You idiot!

430
00:36:46,000 --> 00:36:46,680
Oh, no, Master!

431
00:36:46,680 --> 00:36:47,720
Why did you bring it to me, you dirty rat?

432
00:36:48,600 --> 00:36:51,360
You think I care about this kind of stuff?

433
00:36:51,360 --> 00:36:54,640
(…regarding the leaked photo,)

434
00:36:55,200 --> 00:36:57,160
You dirty rat, get up!
(let’s hear it from the Prime Minister.)

435
00:36:57,720 --> 00:36:58,600
You seeing this?

436
00:36:59,440 --> 00:37:01,240
Do you see what that jerk is doing to me?

437
00:37:01,960 --> 00:37:05,040
(Regarding the Bao Cheng case, nothing is currently urgent.)

438
00:37:05,040 --> 00:37:07,200
(We trust in the justice system.)

439
00:37:07,200 --> 00:37:10,200
(There’s been a complaint, and we’ve acknowledged it.)

440
00:37:11,120 --> 00:37:19,080
(Sir, there’s a speculation that the leaked photo is being swept under the rug.)

441
00:37:19,280 --> 00:37:19,600
(That’s right.)

442
00:37:19,680 --> 00:37:20,760
(Yes, sir. The leaked photo.)

443
00:37:20,800 --> 00:37:24,560
(Right now the photo is irrelevant.)

444
00:37:24,800 --> 00:37:27,160
(As for the continuous raids on…)

445
00:37:27,600 --> 00:37:28,560
Master.

446
00:37:29,400 --> 00:37:32,200
Isn’t this problem negotiable?

447
00:37:32,720 --> 00:37:35,800
You simply need to talk to the Prime Minister.

448
00:37:35,920 --> 00:37:37,480
I was familiar with him, alright!

449
00:37:37,960 --> 00:37:39,440
He took my money for his election campaign!

450
00:37:40,040 --> 00:37:41,560
But now he’s hellbent on getting me killed!

451
00:37:41,960 --> 00:37:43,320
You think he’s gonna talk to me?

452
00:37:45,120 --> 00:37:46,040
Damn it!

453
00:37:46,160 --> 00:37:49,520
(The denaturalization of his citizenship is in accordance with legal processes,)

454
00:37:49,520 --> 00:37:52,520
(and has nothing to do with any political affiliations.)

455
00:37:56,680 --> 00:38:01,400
Then we just have to make him want to talk to us.

456
00:38:03,160 --> 00:38:03,920
How?

457
00:38:07,360 --> 00:38:09,120
It will require money.

458
00:38:10,240 --> 00:38:10,880
And…

459
00:38:11,560 --> 00:38:14,360
It will likely be a little risky.

460
00:38:16,400 --> 00:38:17,240
I don’t care!

461
00:38:18,560 --> 00:38:19,920
I’m not scared of risks!

462
00:38:21,280 --> 00:38:22,720
Just make sure he leaves me alone.

463
00:38:23,320 --> 00:38:24,800
I’ll do whatever needs to be done!

464
00:38:33,840 --> 00:38:35,200
Next on today’s news,

465
00:38:35,240 --> 00:38:38,240
the current political climate seems more tumultuous than previously speculated.
POLITICS IN CRISIS! PROTESTERS DEMAND RESIGNATION

466
00:38:38,480 --> 00:38:39,480
- Get out!
- Get out!
WE DON’T WANT A CORRUPTED PRIME MINISTER

467
00:38:39,480 --> 00:38:40,480
- Get out!
- Get out!
SAY NO TO CORRUPTED DEMOCRACY

468
00:38:40,480 --> 00:38:42,080
Are you angry?

469
00:38:42,080 --> 00:38:43,720
We are enraged!

470
00:38:44,120 --> 00:38:46,920
DISSOLVE ,RESIGN
We need to demand a transparent government.

471
00:38:47,040 --> 00:38:49,680
We’ll get rid of all the corruption!

472
00:38:49,800 --> 00:38:51,280
Wipe the country free of grays!

473
00:38:51,360 --> 00:38:53,160
We’ll be clean!

474
00:38:53,680 --> 00:38:57,440
The number of protesters is now growing.

475
00:38:57,680 --> 00:38:59,040
Is it true that more than ten thousand people have come out?

476
00:38:59,040 --> 00:38:59,960
It’s more than a hundred thousand.

477
00:39:01,120 --> 00:39:02,760
DISSOLVE THE PARLIAMENT. RESIGN.
POWER BACK TO THE PEOPLE.

478
00:39:02,960 --> 00:39:03,800
Don’t argue!

479
00:39:04,000 --> 00:39:04,520
No!

480
00:39:05,840 --> 00:39:06,640
Flight attendant.

481
00:39:06,680 --> 00:39:07,520
You?

482
00:39:07,560 --> 00:39:09,680
You’re insane.

483
00:39:12,360 --> 00:39:13,120
Let’s try it.

484
00:39:13,800 --> 00:39:15,160
Show me.

485
00:39:16,160 --> 00:39:18,240
Why don’t we have a proper lunch somewhere off campus, Ploy?

486
00:39:18,760 --> 00:39:20,360
I told you it’s my treat.

487
00:39:22,360 --> 00:39:23,160
I have an afternoon class.

488
00:39:23,520 --> 00:39:24,120
I don’t want to be late.

489
00:39:31,760 --> 00:39:32,760
Did you join these protests?

490
00:39:35,240 --> 00:39:35,760
Why?

491
00:39:39,280 --> 00:39:40,000
Nothing.

492
00:39:43,080 --> 00:39:44,600
Just be careful.

493
00:39:57,280 --> 00:40:00,320
You should end your lease and move back home next month.

494
00:40:06,080 --> 00:40:08,240
I’m sure I can buy the house back from our uncle this time.

495
00:40:08,720 --> 00:40:10,440
I already gave him a one-million deposit.

496
00:40:12,320 --> 00:40:14,440
That’s not even half of the value of the house.

497
00:40:15,280 --> 00:40:17,200
How are you going to make enough money to pay for the rest?

498
00:40:22,040 --> 00:40:23,320
How could you say that?

499
00:40:24,600 --> 00:40:25,760
I got that one million.

500
00:40:25,760 --> 00:40:27,560
You think I wouldn’t be able to pay for the rest of it?

501
00:40:30,440 --> 00:40:32,240
Don’t you dare act up here, Pete.

502
00:40:33,240 --> 00:40:34,160
Act up?

503
00:40:34,680 --> 00:40:35,040
Hey!

504
00:40:35,400 --> 00:40:36,880
What do you mean by ‘act up’?

505
00:40:37,160 --> 00:40:38,320
Talk to me!

506
00:40:39,440 --> 00:40:40,120
Hey!

507
00:40:40,760 --> 00:40:41,800
Can you shut up for a sec?

508
00:40:42,000 --> 00:40:42,720
You shut up!

509
00:40:45,800 --> 00:40:47,440
And stop being so troublesome.

510
00:40:48,160 --> 00:40:48,720
Please.

511
00:41:13,160 --> 00:41:14,200
Just leave it by the door.

512
00:41:28,040 --> 00:41:29,560
I paid for the food already.

513
00:41:35,880 --> 00:41:36,440
Jiejie.

514
00:41:38,080 --> 00:41:38,680
Didi.

515
00:42:04,400 --> 00:42:05,200
I’m not making tea.

516
00:42:05,400 --> 00:42:05,880
Too lazy to.

517
00:42:06,160 --> 00:42:06,840
You’ll just have to drink it off a bottle.

518
00:42:10,400 --> 00:42:13,720
Your quality of life has been incessantly sinking, hasn't it?

519
00:42:16,400 --> 00:42:19,640
Apologies for not divining your arrival beforehand, Madam.

520
00:42:20,000 --> 00:42:22,960
Forgive me for having to receive you in such a shabby room.

521
00:42:25,400 --> 00:42:26,240
Shabby?

522
00:42:27,040 --> 00:42:29,600
This is much more than you deserve,

523
00:42:30,040 --> 00:42:31,680
considering the life you’re living.

524
00:42:31,800 --> 00:42:35,480
Well, unlike you, I don’t have the privilege
of having a politician as a patron.

525
00:42:39,680 --> 00:42:41,280
So you stoop to making deals with thieves?

526
00:42:48,040 --> 00:42:50,160
At least I’m not using my power to serve someone.

527
00:42:54,440 --> 00:42:55,480
I’m not serving him.

528
00:42:56,680 --> 00:42:57,720
I’m supporting him.

529
00:42:59,520 --> 00:43:01,040
Because he makes me stronger.

530
00:43:06,400 --> 00:43:07,000
Forget it.

531
00:43:09,920 --> 00:43:11,120
I’m not here to pick a fight.

532
00:43:12,040 --> 00:43:13,080
I need your help.

533
00:43:15,600 --> 00:43:16,880
You know what’s happened, don’t you?

534
00:43:24,120 --> 00:43:25,960
A man comes into power because of his people.

535
00:43:27,000 --> 00:43:28,600
He can be driven away because of his people, too.

536
00:43:29,800 --> 00:43:31,160
It is the natural course of things.

537
00:43:32,760 --> 00:43:33,760
That’s not the case.

538
00:43:34,520 --> 00:43:38,080
You’re well aware nothing is natural about this.

539
00:43:39,400 --> 00:43:41,280
It’s clearly the influence of a demon.

540
00:44:17,240 --> 00:44:17,800
Deal.

541
00:44:32,960 --> 00:44:33,920
Thank you.

542
00:44:35,520 --> 00:44:36,040
For?

543
00:44:36,640 --> 00:44:37,400
For the meal.

544
00:44:38,480 --> 00:44:39,080
What?

545
00:44:39,560 --> 00:44:40,560
When did I agree to that?

546
00:44:41,280 --> 00:44:42,160
Now, apparently.

547
00:44:42,800 --> 00:44:44,560
I just agreed to work for you.

548
00:44:44,600 --> 00:44:45,200
Damn.

549
00:44:45,200 --> 00:44:46,640
What’s the big deal? It’s just dinner.

550
00:44:52,600 --> 00:44:54,400
Oh, this troubling you?

551
00:44:54,880 --> 00:44:56,200
You’re filthy rich!

552
00:44:56,400 --> 00:44:57,240
I’m not troubled.

553
00:44:58,800 --> 00:45:00,240
Well, if you’re not, then smile.

554
00:45:00,440 --> 00:45:01,240
Give me a smile.

555
00:45:02,720 --> 00:45:03,320
What for?

556
00:45:04,080 --> 00:45:06,000
To prove that you’re not feeling troubled.

557
00:45:06,560 --> 00:45:08,480
My life is way worse than yours,

558
00:45:08,480 --> 00:45:10,000
and I don't look half as constipated as you do.

559
00:45:11,280 --> 00:45:11,720
Well?

560
00:45:11,880 --> 00:45:12,520
Smile.

561
00:45:15,440 --> 00:45:17,560
Oh, wow. It’s beyond him.

562
00:45:18,520 --> 00:45:19,160
You idiot…

563
00:45:19,800 --> 00:45:21,720
Not only are you leeching me off,
you’re also ridiculous.

564
00:45:22,320 --> 00:45:25,040
It’s just for laughs, man.

565
00:45:25,560 --> 00:45:27,440
You know, it’s ice-breaking.

566
00:45:29,440 --> 00:45:31,720
You can’t even give me a smile, buddy.

567
00:45:33,960 --> 00:45:34,560
“Buddy”?

568
00:45:37,400 --> 00:45:39,440
You and I are buddies?

569
00:45:41,240 --> 00:45:42,800
I don’t like being distant.

570
00:45:43,040 --> 00:45:45,000
And I am no one’s lackey.

571
00:45:45,280 --> 00:45:48,200
So we are friends.

572
00:45:51,440 --> 00:45:52,000
What?

573
00:45:53,400 --> 00:45:54,720
You don’t want to be my friend?

574
00:46:28,480 --> 00:46:29,840
Brotherhood bites.

575
00:46:38,160 --> 00:46:39,320
Cheers, buddy!

576
00:46:41,280 --> 00:46:42,600
What a goofball.

577
00:46:44,000 --> 00:46:46,200
Gotta love having a full belly and a full pocket.

578
00:46:46,320 --> 00:46:47,960
If we’re friends, we split the bill, you jerk.

579
00:46:49,280 --> 00:46:51,400
But you have way more money!

580
00:46:53,240 --> 00:46:54,520
Shut up and eat.

581
00:46:54,640 --> 00:46:55,480
This place really knows how to cook.

582
00:46:56,120 --> 00:46:57,280
You haven’t tried the jellyfish, huh?

583
00:46:57,560 --> 00:46:58,120
Eat up.

584
00:46:58,480 --> 00:46:59,560
If it’s good, you eat up.

585
00:47:00,080 --> 00:47:01,040
Let me try that in your bowl.

586
00:47:01,040 --> 00:47:02,520
How long are you gonna keep stalking me?

587
00:47:02,520 --> 00:47:04,440
Come on. Just help me out. I beg you.

588
00:47:04,440 --> 00:47:06,080
You know, you might just be able to do it.

589
00:47:06,080 --> 00:47:07,000
You think too highly of me.

590
00:47:07,120 --> 00:47:08,200
Fine! Forget it!

591
00:47:08,800 --> 00:47:10,320
That still doesn’t make you any less Wu.

592
00:47:10,320 --> 00:47:11,720
Don’t freaking call me Wu.

593
00:47:12,400 --> 00:47:13,480
If you’re no Wu,

594
00:47:13,560 --> 00:47:14,400
what are you?

595
00:47:16,400 --> 00:47:17,200
I have a big job,

596
00:47:17,400 --> 00:47:19,560
and I need to borrow the power of the demon inside you.

597
00:47:19,560 --> 00:47:20,680
You will need a little training, though.

598
00:47:21,960 --> 00:47:24,520
You need to use its power to locate Qi Rong.

599
00:47:24,600 --> 00:47:27,520
Most importantly, do not let the demon devour you.
